        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2019-05-15 01:06:38.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> How is this different from \"max_sectors_kb=0\"?\n\nYup, this should disable max_sectors_kb tune, but still scheduler there? and possibly\nnew auto tune added in the future.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "fb402b2fdbf36cbfd0a13e52a2475afa775e2af4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 541,
        "name": "Gu Zheng",
        "email": "gzheng@ddn.com",
        "username": "cengku9660",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2019-05-15 01:45:17.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\n(2 comments)\n\nI think we'd better to control the tune from mount_lustre rather than only ldsikfs side.\nThe major goal of this option is let lustre free from backend storage tuning, and give a chance to manage-utils or admin (out of native lustre, e.g  Exascalser from DDN) who are more professional and proficient in tuning field to take over the job.\nActually tune to zfs is more complex than ldiskfs, and this option is also very useful to osd-zfs sites.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "4c9ae43a8b4349082d6a041e13683ec5c0692422",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 428,
