    {
      "id": "bbf1d505cff027fcc22dece93d6d955a5839791f",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2019-05-24 03:52:11.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> > How is this different from \"max_sectors_kb=0\"?\n > \n > Yup, this should disable max_sectors_kb tune, but still scheduler\n > there? and possibly new auto tune added in the future.\n\nWhat scheduler is in use that is being auto-tuned differently?  There was already a patch landed to allow mq-deadline as an acceptable scheduler, and I don't think we will be adding any other kinds of auto-tuning in the future, so this doesn't seem any better than setting max_sectors_kb=0, which already exists for all releases.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "c62ca2d2b11c0a8811746bcff264a0a4b6409cce",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 428,
        "name": "Wang Shilong",
        "email": "wangshilong1991@gmail.com",
        "username": "wangshilong",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2019-05-24 04:38:22.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> > > How is this different from \"max_sectors_kb=0\"?\n > >\n > > Yup, this should disable max_sectors_kb tune, but still scheduler\n > > there? and possibly new auto tune added in the future.\n > \n > What scheduler is in use that is being auto-tuned differently? \n > There was already a patch landed to allow mq-deadline as an\n > acceptable scheduler, and I don't think we will be adding any other\n > kinds of auto-tuning in the future, so this doesn't seem any better\n > than setting max_sectors_kb=0, which already exists for all\n > releases.\n\nActually, currently max_seccots_kb=0 doesn't mean it won't do nothing, instead it read existed\n@max_sectors_kb and write it again with it(even it doesn't change anything)\n\nI am not sure whether this could cause messy value, maybe we could ask Arthur to test if this could Solve His problem for DDN exscaler problem.\n\nOr we could improve the case that max_seccots_kb=0 did nothing?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "db807aa390264dfde408c5ccd6b0a3afd41cd7a5",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
